The paper deals with algorithmic information measures, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Turing machines and program-size complexity also suggests a connection to the theory of computation (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lossless compression algorithms (cs.CR) and includes a numerical implementation of the Coding Theorem Method (cs.LG).
